  <description><![CDATA[<p>The small, authentic city of <a data-udi="umb://document/387b9a048e564a54b4daf68ada0e270f" href="/{localLink:umb://document/387b9a048e564a54b4daf68ada0e270f}" title="Stavanger">Stavanger</a> is home to the Lysefjord, the impressive Pulpit Rock and some of southern Norway’s best walking terrain, whilst vibrant <a data-udi="umb://document/d517b2c21fa94eb096a3bcb6b7e933c5" href="/{localLink:umb://document/d517b2c21fa94eb096a3bcb6b7e933c5}" title="Bergen">Bergen</a> with its historic colourful Bryggen Wharf and Fløiban funicular is a must for most visitors to the fjords. This holiday combines these 2 popular, yet contrasting cities, taking in some of the best-known attractions in Fjord Norway along the way as well as a memorable and scenic coastal cruise on the new ferry route linking the two ports with breakfast on board.</p>
<p> </p>
